sometimes you're kind of worried

00:38:31.750 --> 00:38:33.550
about these documentaries
because it's

00:38:33.550 --> 00:38:36.670
like your people are painted
as helpless folks just looking

00:38:36.670 --> 00:38:39.760
for help, looking for
outsiders to intervene.

00:38:39.760 --> 00:38:41.110
That's not the case.

00:38:41.110 --> 00:38:42.370
There are Congolese
solutions on the ground.

00:38:42.370 --> 00:38:44.203
There are Congolese who
really want to work,

00:38:44.203 --> 00:38:48.040
but there are powers that be a
lot of times from very wealthy

00:38:48.040 --> 00:38:52.135
interests with big money, real
money, that really cannot--

00:38:52.135 --> 00:38:55.720
that really would be hurt by
Congo taking control of its

00:38:55.720 --> 00:38:56.860
resources.

00:38:56.860 --> 00:38:59.320
So there's a lot of
major interests at heart.

00:38:59.320 --> 00:39:01.720
So it's really important
that to just also

00:39:01.720 --> 00:39:03.010
be aware that the Congolese--

00:39:03.010 --> 00:39:04.509
I just want to make
sure that people

00:39:04.509 --> 00:39:07.150
don't leave this
thinking, poor Congo,

00:39:07.150 --> 00:39:08.740
I feel bad for the Congolese.

00:39:08.740 --> 00:39:10.020
They're in really bad shape.

00:39:10.020 --> 00:39:12.370
There are some problems, but
also there's a lot of pride

00:39:12.370 --> 00:39:13.060
there.

00:39:13.060 --> 00:39:15.700
And as Congolese, we definitely
want to make sure that people--

00:39:15.700 --> 00:39:19.249
that perception of us as a
poor, helpless bunch of people

00:39:19.249 --> 00:39:21.790
doesn't exist, that we don't--
we want to make sure that kind

00:39:21.790 --> 00:39:22.464
of stops.

00:39:22.464 --> 00:39:24.880
But that if you want to support
that, again, you check out

00:39:24.880 --> 00:39:26.550
the resources, make
sure you understand

00:39:26.550 --> 00:39:28.720
where your 401ks going,
that you make sure

00:39:28.720 --> 00:39:31.660
that if you want to support
an activist, then do that.

00:39:31.660 --> 00:39:33.825
And also one last thing
specifically to Google--

00:39:33.825 --> 00:39:35.950
when I was in Congo basically,
the American Chamber

00:39:35.950 --> 00:39:37.840
of Commerce told me
that Google will be

00:39:37.840 --> 00:39:39.800
going to Congo this December.

00:39:39.800 --> 00:39:43.000
They'll be helping set
up some fiber optics,

00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:47.530
I guess wiring and cables to
make for Wi-Fi connectivity.

00:39:47.530 --> 00:39:50.230
So again, I don't know how close
Google here and Google in Congo

00:39:50.230 --> 00:39:53.796
works but basically, I think
it will be great if when

00:39:53.796 --> 00:39:55.420
Google is in the
country that they make

00:39:55.420 --> 00:39:57.070
sure that they employ locals.

00:39:57.070 --> 00:39:59.929
A lot of times foreign
companies they go elsewhere,

00:39:59.929 --> 00:40:01.720
and they just bring
their people with them,

00:40:01.720 --> 00:40:03.880
and they don't have as
much as big of an impact

00:40:03.880 --> 00:40:06.110
as they could in a
local population.

00:40:06.110 --> 00:40:08.260
So basically, if any
of you are interested

00:40:08.260 --> 00:40:11.077
or are aware of how Google
Congo would operate,

00:40:11.077 --> 00:40:13.660
I definitely want to encourage
you to maybe talk to your team,

00:40:13.660 --> 00:40:15.076
talk to your leaders
and make sure

00:40:15.076 --> 00:40:17.470
that there is a plan
in place to ensure

00:40:17.470 --> 00:40:20.200
that when goes is in
Congo, it has as much

00:40:20.200 --> 00:40:23.270
of a positive effect as it can.

00:40:23.270 --> 00:40:23.770
Thank you.

00:40:23.770 --> 00:40:26.820
[APPLAUSE]

